<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently, the router and dispatcher are instantiated and initialized prior to the dispatch cycle -- meaning several things:
* No way to inject substitutions prior to routing/dispatch
* No way to add front controller parameters via plugins and have them injected</p>

<p>An easy way to correct the situation is to:
* have the get*() methods lazyload default objects
* always use a get() method to retrieve the required object in order to perform the required dispatch operation</p>

